Maybe a food critic or something.

850
00:40:21.836 --> 00:40:23.086
You put ketchup on your steak.

851
00:40:23.087 --> 00:40:24.421
I'll come in. and they'll be like.

852
00:40:24.422 --> 00:40:25.922
"Hey. aren't you the food guy?"

853
00:40:25.923 --> 00:40:27.633
And I'll say. "Please. call me Three-Bite Bailey."

854
00:40:27.634 --> 00:40:29.092
And then they will serve me a four-course meal.

855
00:40:29.093 --> 00:40:30.969
and I'll pull out my wallet. and they'll say.

856
00:40:30.970 --> 00:40:33.555
"No. no. no. sir. please. tonight. on the house."

857
00:40:33.556 --> 00:40:34.765
And then I get paid.

858
00:40:34.766 --> 00:40:36.516
Is that how that goes?

859
00:40:36.517 --> 00:40:38.518
- I actually don't know.
- (both laughing)

860
00:40:38.519 --> 00:40:40.520
Okay. my little food critic.

861
00:40:40.521 --> 00:40:41.772
what's the verdict on this bread?

862
00:40:41.773 --> 00:40:43.482
- This bread?
- Mm-hmm.

863
00:40:43.483 --> 00:40:44.858
Oh.

864
00:40:44.859 --> 00:40:46.736
Well...

865
00:40:49.030 --> 00:40:52.616
Hmm. Slightly stale. but the butter makes up for that shit.

866
00:40:52.617 --> 00:40:54.493
- Profound.
- That'll be a hundred dollars.

867
00:40:54.494 --> 00:40:55.744
(laughs) Well...

868
00:40:55.745 --> 00:40:57.747
- (cell phone vibrating)
- Sorry.

869
00:40:59.040 --> 00:41:00.666
It's the second time he's called.

870
00:41:00.667 --> 00:41:02.001
I'll be right back.

871
00:41:03.002 --> 00:41:06.004
- What is it. dude? I'm busy.
- IAN: Oh. busy doing Nikki?

872
00:41:06.005 --> 00:41:07.339
What do you want?

873
00:41:07.340 --> 00:41:09.966
Okay. so. um...

874
00:41:09.967 --> 00:41:11.677
- What is it?
- (Ian stammers)

875
00:41:11.678 --> 00:41:13.136
I'm not gonna tell Sarah about this.

876
00:41:13.137 --> 00:41:16.056
because I don't want to spread drama.

877
00:41:16.057 --> 00:41:18.975
I looked into Nikki's dad having cancer.

878
00:41:18.976 --> 00:41:21.478
and he's healthy as a baby.

879
00:41:21.479 --> 00:41:23.815
He's been to work. like. every day.

880
00:41:29.904 --> 00:41:31.697
Why would she lie about that. Ian?

881
00:41:31.698 --> 00:41:33.156
I don't know. For attention.

882
00:41:33.157 --> 00:41:34.866
I called the hospital she told me about.

883
00:41:34.867 --> 00:41:37.536
and they didn't even know who I was talking about.

884
00:41:37.537 --> 00:41:40.455
Look. you know I always got your back on this stuff.

885
00:41:40.456 --> 00:41:44.584
Apparently. Nikki and Sarah had a conversation about you

886
00:41:44.585 --> 00:41:46.002
that-that day you weren't in.

887
00:41:46.003 --> 00:41:48.839
and. uh. Nikki said she just thought of you

888
00:41:48.840 --> 00:41:51.258
like her little brother or. you know.

889
00:41:51.259 --> 00:41:52.551
and she. like. friend-zoned you.

890
00:41:52.552 --> 00:41:54.594
And-and-and look. that may suck to hear.

891
00:41:54.595 --> 00:41:56.304
but I just think you got to know because.

892
00:41:56.305 --> 00:41:58.807
I-I don't know. I think she has some kind of ill intentions

893
00:41:58.808 --> 00:42:01.268
or something freaking mental is going on. man.

894
00:42:01.269 --> 00:42:03.019
And maybe Sarah's jealous and made that up.

895
00:42:03.020 --> 00:42:05.731
but. like. even if you take that out of the equation.

896
00:42:05.732 --> 00:42:08.859
this is strange. dude.

897
00:42:08.860 --> 00:42:11.111
It's like Nikki snapped into a different person.

898
00:42:11.112 --> 00:42:14.030
Sh-She's all of a sudden infatuated with you.

899
00:42:14.031 --> 00:42:16.075
♪♪

900
00:42:30.047 --> 00:42:31.883
Everything okay?

901
00:42:37.764 --> 00:42:40.224
(voice trembling): Nikki. do you...

902
00:42:42.185 --> 00:42:44.145
What?

903
00:42:45.313 --> 00:42:47.314
Never mind.

904
00:42:47.315 --> 00:42:49.733
I have something for you.

905
00:42:49.734 --> 00:42:51.944
- What is it?
- Um...

906
00:43:00.369 --> 00:43:01.871
What is it?

907
00:43:03.623 --> 00:43:05.750
Open it.

908
00:43:11.088 --> 00:43:13.965
It's a... it's a tiger's eye.

909
00:43:13.966 --> 00:43:16.343
- Wow.
- It was my mom's.

910
00:43:16.344 --> 00:43:18.512
and then it was mine.

911
00:43:18.513 --> 00:43:23.934
It's supposed to bring you confidence and willpower. so...

912
00:43:23.935 --> 00:43:26.229
now you can be a food critic.

913
00:43:28.898 --> 00:43:30.690
Why are you giving it to me?

914
00:43:30.691 --> 00:43:34.736
Bear. I love you so. so. so. so. so much.

915
00:43:34.737 --> 00:43:37.114
I don't think I could live without you.

916
00:43:41.619 --> 00:43:44.622
You love me more than anyone in the world?

917
00:43:48.626 --> 00:43:51.087
(chuckling): Yes. more than anyone.

918
00:43:54.465 --> 00:43:55.925
Nikki.

919
00:43:57.093 --> 00:43:58.760
Yeah?

920
00:43:58.761 --> 00:44:00.762
Does your dad really have cancer?

921
00:44:00.763 --> 00:44:02.974
♪♪

922
00:44:15.319 --> 00:44:16.696
No.

923
00:44:20.116 --> 00:44:22.659
(chuckling): No. no. no.

924
00:44:22.660 --> 00:44:23.785
What?

925
00:44:23.786 --> 00:44:25.745
No. no. no.

926
00:44:25.746 --> 00:44:28.081
- no. no. no. no. no.
- What?

927
00:44:28.082 --> 00:44:29.791
- Don't do that!
- Nikki. (Stammers)

928
00:44:29.792 --> 00:44:32.335
- I thought we were having a nice date.
- (Patrons murmuring)

929
00:44:32.336 --> 00:44:34.170
- We-we are. We are. Sit down.
- Why does it matter?

930
00:44:34.171 --> 00:44:37.632
- I thought we were having a nice date.
- We are. We are.

931
00:44:37.633 --> 00:44:39.467
- We are. We are.
- (Nikki crying)

932
00:44:39.468 --> 00:44:41.595
It's okay.

933
00:44:41.596 --> 00:44:44.098
We are. We are.

934
00:44:53.941 --> 00:44:55.985
Then why does it matter?

935
00:45:03.951 --> 00:45:05.493
It doesn't matter to me.

936
00:45:05.494 --> 00:45:08.038
(grunts) Oh. yeah.

937
00:45:08.039 --> 00:45:10.374
(grunting. moaning)

938
00:45:11.959 --> 00:45:14.837
- (Bear grunting)
- Yeah. Uh-huh.

939
00:45:15.713 --> 00:45:17.924
(moaning)

940
00:45:19.383 --> 00:45:21.301
(breathing heavily)

941
00:45:21.302 --> 00:45:23.930
- Oh. that was amazing. baby.
- Yeah.

942
00:45:26.766 --> 00:45:28.351
Yeah.

943
00:45:37.818 --> 00:45:40.112
(takes deep breath)

944
00:46:00.549 --> 00:46:02.051
Nikki?

945
00:46:16.399 --> 00:46:18.859
- NIKKI: Go back to sleep.
- (Bear gasps)

946
00:46:20.069 --> 00:46:21.779
BEAR: Nikki.

947
00:46:26.158 --> 00:46:28.202
What are you doing?

948
00:46:33.958 --> 00:46:35.959
What are you doing?

949
00:46:35.960 --> 00:46:37.920
